8 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 37-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
9 and enacted as follows:
10 Meals provided to employees of the veterans' home.
11 In the event of a disruption of operations, the veterans' home may provide meals at a fair
12 value or without a charge to employees of the veterans' home as required by the job
13 assignments of the employees.
14 SECTION 4. EXEMPTION - LINE ITEM TRANSFERS - REPORT. Notwithstanding section
15 54-16-04, the director of the office of management and budget may transfer up to $600,000
16 from special funds from the salaries and wages line item to the operating expenses line item in
17 section 1 of chapter 7 of the 2023 Session Laws, during the period beginning with the effective
18 date of this Act, and ending June 30, 2025, as requested by the veterans' home. The veterans'
19 home shall notify the legislative council of any transfers made pursuant to this section.
20 SECTION 5. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - VETERANS' HOME FACILITIES.
21 During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying the usage of the
22 veterans' home facilities. The study must consider any organizational changes necessary to
23 increase resident census at the veterans' home, potential uses for unoccupied space, and
24 federal requirements. The legislative management shall report its findings and
25 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
26 the seventieth legislative assembly.
27 SECTION 6. EMERGENCY. Section 4 of this Act and the sum of $175,000 appropriated
28 from the Melvin Norgard memorial fund for resident garages and storage units in the other
29 funds line item in section 1 of this Act are declared to be an emergency measure.
